Sessionn 4:
1. Make  a virtual Environment in python : python -m venv .venv 
2. Actiate Virtual Environment
3. Go to the root folder and install django : pip install django 
4. Create a django project : django-admin startproject  my-django-project
5. Go to the project root Folder 
6. and make app inside the project root folder: python manage.py startapp firstapp
7. import your  project directory into the vscode
8. Register your app in settings.py 
9. Make a template folder inside the project  directory . 
10. make the temp dir : TEMP_DIR = BASE_DIR/'templates'
11. Insert TEMP_DIR in  your templates_list
12. Make new folder inside the templates folder named your app name (e.g firstapp) and create the index.html file 
13. make the static folder inside the project  directory.
14. configure  static in settings.py 
    STATIC_DIR = BASE_DIR/'static'
    STATICFILES_DIRS = [STATIC_DIR,]
15. Write you first views inside the views.py in firstapp 
16. configure app  level urls
17. congiure project based urls
18. Run your server : python manage.py runserver
19. check your html is working or not by taking boiler plate int templates/firstapp/index.html file
20. make 3 folder css,img and js inside static folder
21. make sample css code file in templates/css/css_file
22. Link css file in html file: <link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/index.css'%}">
23. Load static Files : {% load static %} jst  below the <!DOCTYPE html>
24. Create your first model inheriting models.Model in your Model Class.
25. Create  python code into SQL code: python manage.py makemigrations
26. Convert SQL code into Databse table : python manage.py migrate.
27. Create superuser : python manage.py createsuperuser
28. Check django superadmin dashboard.: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
29. Register your model in admin.py: admin.site.register(Model_name) ==> Don't forget to import your model.
30. Convert object into string by def__str__(self)
31. Import db object in  your views.py my_obj = Employee.objects.all(), context = {"my_obj":my_obj}
32. Capture your object from html file using {{key}}
33. Create forms.py in application folder
